***** Required Texts *****
[Amazon_logo] Klaus, C., et al. In Depth: Essayists for Our Time. 2nd ed.
Princeton, NJ: Heinle, 1993. ISBN: 9780155001725.
[Amazon_logo] Lopate, Phillip. The Art of the Personal Essay. Anchor; 1st
Anchor Books Pbk. Ed edition, 1997. ISBN: 9780385423397.
[Amazon_logo] Queenan, Joe, ed. The Malcontents: The Best Bitter, Cynical, and
Satirical Writing in the World. Philadelphia, PA: Running Press Book
Publishers, 2004. ISBN: 9780762416974.
[Amazon_logo] Raymo, Chet. "An Ancient Brilliance." In The Soul of the Night:
An Astronomical Pilgrimage. Englewood Cliffs, N.J.: Prentice Hall, 1985, pp.
53-62. ISBN: 9780138228835.
[Amazon_logo] Alexie, Sherman. "Captivity." In The Next American Essay. Edited
by John D'Agata. St. Paul, Minn.: Greywolf Press, 2002, pp. 63-69. ISBN:
9781555973759.
Photocopied essays provided by instructor.
